_article_star.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/bc/Featured_article_star.svg/32px-Featured_article_star.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="180" data-file-height="180" /></a></span>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Portal:Scientology" title="Portal:Scientology">Scientology</a>&#160;</li>\n<li>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Portal:Shinto" title="Portal:Shinto">Shinto</a>&#160;</li>\n<li>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Portal:Theosophy" title="Portal:Theosophy">Theosophy</a>&#160;</li>\n<li>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Portal:Wicca" title="Portal:Wicca">Wicca</a>&#160;</li>\n<li>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Portal:Zoroastrianism" title="Portal:Zoroastrianism">Zoroastrianism</a>&#160;</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<table width="100%" cellpadding="5" cellspacing="10" style="background:#ccffff; border-style:solid; border-width:3px; border-color: #66cccc;">\n<tr>\n<td width="55%" style="vertical-align:top;padding: 0; margin:0;">\n<div style="float:right; width:100%">\n<div style="clear: both; border: solid #2e8b57; border-width: 1px 1px 0; background: #31644d; color: #ffffff; padding: .1em;padding-top: .1em;padding-left: .1em;padding-right: .1em;padding-bottom: .1em;text-align: center;font-family: sans-serif;font-size:100%;margin-bottom: 0px;">\n<div class="plainlinks" style="float:right;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size:80%; color: #ffffff"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Qur%27an/Intro&amp;action=edit"><span style="color: #ffffff">edit</span></a>&#160;&#160;</div>\n<h2 style="font-family:sans-serif; font-size:100%; font-weight:bold; border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em; color:#ffffff;"><span class="mw-headline" id="Qur.27an_Portal">Qur\'an Portal</span></h2>\n</div>\n<div style="border: 1px solid #2e8b57; border-top-width: 1px; vertical-align: top;background: #f8fffc;opacity: 1; color: #000000; text-align: left; margin: 0 0 10px; padding: 1em;padding-top: .3em;">\n<div style="float:right;margin-left:1em">\n<center><a href="/wiki/Uthman_Qur%27an" class="mw-redirect" title="Uthman Qur\'an">Uthman Qur\'an</a></center>\n<p><a href="/wiki/File:Uthman_Koran_Taschkent_a.jpg" class="image" title="The Samarkand manuscript, now kept in Tashkent."><img alt="The Samarkand manuscript, now kept in Tashkent." src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5b/Uthman_Koran_Taschkent_a.jpg/200px-Uthman_Koran_Taschkent_a.jpg" width="200" height="107" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5b/Uthman_Koran_Taschkent_a.jpg/300px-Uthman_Koran_Taschkent_a.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5b/Uthman_Koran_Taschkent_a.jpg/400px-Uthman_Koran_Taschkent_a.jpg 2x" data-file-width="1330" data-file-height="710" /></a><br /></p>\n</div>\n<p><br />\nThe <b>Holy Qur\xe2\x80\x99an</b> (pronounced <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA"><a href="/wiki/Help:IPA/Arabic" title="Help:IPA/Arabic">[qur\xcb\x88\xca\x94a\xcb\x90n]</a></span>; <a href="/wiki/Arabic_language" class="mw-redirect" title="Arabic language">Arabic</a>: <span lang="ar" dir="rtl" xml:lang="ar"><b>\xd8\xa7\xd9\x84\xd9\x82\xd8\xb1\xd8\xa2\xd9\x86</b></span>\xe2\x80\x8e\xe2\x80\x8e <i><span title="DIN 31635 Arabic" class="Unicode" style="white-space:normal; text-decoration: none">al-qur\xe2\x80\x99\xc4\x81n</span></i>, literally \xe2\x80\x9cthe recitation\xe2\x80\x9d) is the central religious verbal text of <a href="/wiki/Islam" title="Islam">Islam</a>,also sometimes <a href="/wiki/Arabic_transliteration" class="mw-redirect" title="Arabic transliteration">transliterated</a> as <b>Quran</b>, <b>Koran</b>, <b>Qur\xe2\x80\x99\xc4\x81n</b>, or <b>Al-Qur\xe2\x80\x99\xc4\x81n</b>. Muslims believe the Qur\xe2\x80\x99an to be the verbal book of divine guidance and direction for mankind, and consider the original <a href="/wiki/Arabic" title="Arabic">Arabic</a> verbal text to be the final revelation of <a href="/wiki/God" title="God">God</a></p>\n<p>Islam holds that the Qur\xe2\x80\x99an was repeatedly revealed from <a href="/wiki/Allah" title="Allah">Allah</a> to <a href="/wiki/Muhammad" title="Muhammad">Muhammad</a> orally through the angel <a href="/wiki/Gabriel" title="Gabriel">Jibr\xc4\xabl</a> (Gabriel) over a period of approximately twenty-three years, beginning in 610 <a href="/wiki/Common_Era" title="Common Era">CE</a>, when he was forty, and concluding in 632 CE, the year of his death. Followers of Islam further believe that the Qur\xe2\x80\x99an was memorized, recited and written down by Muhammad\'s <a href="/wiki/Sahaba" class="mw-redirect" title="Sahaba">companions</a> after every revelation dictated by <a href="/wiki/Muhammad" title="Muhammad">Muhammad</a>. Most of Muhammad\'s <a href="/wiki/Sahaba" class="mw-redirect" title="Sahaba">companions</a>, tens of thousands, learned the Qur\xe2\x80\x99an by heart, repeatedly recited in front of Muhammad for his approval or the approval of other <a href="/wiki/Sahaba" class="mw-redirect" title="Sahaba">Sahaba</a> Muhammad approved and also compiled it in written form while he was alive. Muslim tradition agrees that although the Qur\xe2\x80\x99an was authentically memorized completely by tens of thousands verbally, the Qur\xe2\x80\x99an was still established textually into a single book form shortly after Muhammad\'s death by order of the first <a href="/wiki/Caliphate" title="Caliphate">Caliph</a> <a href="/wiki/Abu_Bakr" title="Abu Bakr">Abu Bakr</a> suggested by his future successor <a href="/wiki/Umar" title="Umar">Umar</a>. Hafsa, Muhammad\'s widow and Umar\'s daughter, was entrusted with that Quran text after the second Caliph Umar died. When Uthman, the third Caliph, started noticing differences in the <a href="/wiki/Dialect" title="Dialect">dialect</a> of the Qur\xe2\x80\x99an, he requested Hafsa to allow him to use the Qur\xe2\x80\x99an text in her possession to be set as the standard dialect, the <a href="/wiki/Quraysh_(tribe)" class="mw-redirect" title="Quraysh (tribe)">Quraish</a> dialect aka <a href="/wiki/Fus%27ha" class="mw-redirect" title="Fus\'ha">Fus\'ha</a> (<a href="/wiki/Modern_Standard_Arabic" title="Modern Standard Arabic">Modern Standard Arabic</a>). Before returning that Qur\'an text to Hafsa, Uthman immediately made several copies of Abu Bakar\'s Qur\xe2\x80\x99anic compilation and ordered all other texts to be burned. This process of formalization of the orally transmitted text to Abu Bakar\'s Qur\'anic text is known as the "<a href="/wiki/Uthman_Qur%27an" class="mw-redirect" title="Uthman Qur\'an">Uthmanic recension</a>". The present form of the Qur\xe2\x80\x99an text is accepted by most scholars as the original version compiled by Abu Bakr.</p>\n<table width="100%" border="0" style="padding: 0; margin:0; background:transparent;">\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align:right;margin-right:10px;margin-bottom:-4px;"><b><a href="/wiki/Qur%27an" class="mw-redirect" title="Qur\'an">More about Qur\'an...</a></b></td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n<div style="margin:-.8em 0">\n<div class="noprint" style="margin:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; padding:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; text-align:right;"></div>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div style="text-align:center;margin:0.25em 0 0.75em 0"><span class="noprint plainlinks purgelink"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Quran&amp;action=purge"><span title="Purge this page"><b>Show new selections</b></span></a></span></div>\n<div class="portal-column-left">\n<div style="clear: both; border: solid #2e8b57; border-width: 1px 1px 0; background: #31644d; color: #ffffff; padding: .1em;padding-top: .1em;padding-left: .1em;padding-right: .1em;padding-bottom: .1em;text-align: center;font-family: sans-serif;font-size:100%;margin-bottom: 0px;">\n<div class="plainlinks" style="float:right;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size:80%; color: #ffffff"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Quran/Selected_article/2&amp;action=edit"><span style="color: #ffffff">edit</span></a>&#160;&#160;</div>\n<h2 style="font-family:sans-serif; font-size:100%; font-weight:bold; border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em; color:#ffffff;"><span class="mw-headline" id="Selected_article"><i>Selected article</i></span></h2>\n</div>\n<div style="border: 1px solid #2e8b57; border-top-width: 1px; vertical-align: top;background: #f8fffc;opacity: 1; color: #000000; text-align: left; margin: 0 0 10px; padding: 1em;padding-top: .3em;">\n<table style="background: transparent;">\n<tr>\n<td>\n<div style="float:left;margin-right:8px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Human_embryogenesis.png" class="image" title="The initial stages of human embryogenesis"><img alt="The initial stages of human embryogenesis" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8f/Human_embryogenesis.png/100px-Human_embryogenesis.png" width="100" height="80" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8f/Human_embryogenesis.png/150px-Human_embryogenesis.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8f/Human_embryogenesis.png/200px-Human_embryogenesis.png 2x" data-file-width="1197" data-file-height="956" /></a></div>\nThe relation between <b>Qur\'an and science</b> is strongly affirmed in <a href="/wiki/Islam" title="Islam">Islamic</a> thought. Almost all sources, classical and modern, agree that the <a href="/wiki/Qur%E2%80%99an" class="mw-redirect" title="Qur\xe2\x80\x99an">Qur\xe2\x80\x99an</a> encourages the acquisition of science and scientific knowledge.<sup id="cite_ref-EOQ_SAQ_1-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-EOQ_SAQ-1">[1]</a></sup>\n<p>The contemporary Islamic discourse on the Qur\xe2\x80\x99an and science abounds with assertions of the relationship between the two. This presumed relationship is construed in a variety of ways, the most common of which are the efforts to prove the divine nature of the Qur\xe2\x80\x99an through modern science.<sup id="cite_ref-EOQ_SAQ_1-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-EOQ_SAQ-1">[1]</a></sup></p>\n<p>The belief that Qur\'an had <a href="/wiki/Scriptural_foreknowledge" class="mw-redirect" title="Scriptural foreknowledge">prophesied scientific theories and discoveries</a> - known as <b>Ijaz al-Qur\'an</b> - has become a strong and widespread belief in the contemporary Islamic world. Alleged prophecies are often provided to show a connection between the <a href="/wiki/Qur%27an_and_miracles" class="mw-redirect" title="Qur\'an and miracles">Qur\'an and miracles</a>, and to support the belief of divine <a href="/wiki/Origin_and_development_of_the_Qur%27an" class="mw-redirect" title="Origin and development of the Qur\'an">origin for the Qur\'an</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-EOQ_SAQ_1-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-EOQ_SAQ-1">[1]</a></sup></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n<div style="float: left;"><b><a href="/wiki/Portal:Quran/Selected_article" title="Portal:Quran/Selected article">More selected articles...</a></b></div>\n<div style="float: right;"><b><a href="/wiki/Qur%27an_and_science" class="mw-redirect" title="Qur\'an and science">Read more...</a></b></div>\n<p><br /></p>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\n</div>\n<div style="clear: both; border: solid #2e8b57; border-width: 1px 1px 0; background: #31644d; color: #ffffff; padding: .1em;padding-top: .1em;padding-left: .1em;padding-right: .1em;padding-bottom: .1em;text-align: center;font-family: sans-serif;font-size:100%;margin-bottom: 0px;">\n<div class="plainlinks" style="float:right;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size:80%; color: #ffffff"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Quran/Selected_picture/4&amp;action=edit"><span style="color: #ffffff">edit</span></a>&#160;&#160;</div>\n<h2 style="font-family:sans-serif; font-size:100%; font-weight:bold; border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em; color:#ffffff;"><span class="mw-headline" id="Selected_picture"><i>Selected picture</i></span></h2>\n</div>\n<div style="border: 1px solid #2e8b57; border-top-width: 1px; vertical-align: top;background: #f8fffc;opacity: 1; color: #000000; text-align: left; margin: 0 0 10px; padding: 1em;padding-top: .3em;">\n<div style="text-align: center;">\n<div style="display:table; margin: 0 auto 5px auto; padding:7px; border:4px ridge Transparent">\n<div class="center">\n<div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:Bismillah_gold.svg" class="image" title="The first verse of the first surah of the Koran"><img alt="The first verse of the first surah of the Koran" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9a/Bismillah_gold.svg/250px-Bismillah_gold.svg.png" width="250" height="250" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9a/Bismillah_gold.svg/375px-Bismillah_gold.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9a/Bismillah_gold.svg/500px-Bismillah_gold.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="855" data-file-height="855" /></a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="noprint" style="display:table; margin: 0 auto; width:33%;"></div>\n<p>The first verse of the first surah of the Koran</p>\n</div>\n<div class="noprint" style="border:0; padding:0; margin:0;"><span style="display:inline-block; text-align:left; width:32%;"><b><a href="/wiki/Portal:Quran/Selected_picture" title="Portal:Quran/Selected picture">More selected pictures...</a></b></span><span style="display:inline-block; text-align:center; width:34%;">&#160;</span><span style="display:inline-block; text-align:right; width:32%;"><b><a href="/wiki/Bismillah" class="mw-disambig" title="Bismillah">Read more...</a></b></span></div>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="portal-column-right">\n<div style="clear: both; border: solid #2e8b57; border-width: 1px 1px 0; background: #31644d; color: #ffffff; padding: .1em;padding-top: .1em;padding-left: .1em;padding-right: .1em;padding-bottom: .1em;text-align: center;font-family: sans-serif;font-size:100%;margin-bottom: 0px;">\n<div class="plainlinks" style="float:right;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size:80%; color: #ffffff"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Quran/Selected_biography/1&amp;action=edit"><span style="color: #ffffff">edit</span></a>&#160;&#160;</div>\n<h2 style="font-family:sans-serif; font-size:100%; font-weight:bold; border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em; color:#ffffff;"><span class="mw-headline" id="Selected_biography"><i>Selected biography</i></span></h2>\n</div>\n<div style="border: 1px solid #2e8b57; border-top-width: 1px; vertical-align: top;background: #f8fffc;opacity: 1; color: #000000; text-align: left; margin: 0 0 10px; padding: 1em;padding-top: .3em;">\n<p><b>Ali Husayni Sistani</b> (<a href="/wiki/Arabic_language" class="mw-redirect" title="Arabic language">Arabic</a>: <span lang="ar" dir="rtl" xml:lang="ar">\xd8\xb9\xd9\x84\xd9\x8a \xd8\xa7\xd9\x84\xd8\xad\xd8\xb3\xd9\x8a\xd9\x86\xd9\x8a \xd8\xa7\xd9\x84\xd8\xb3\xd9\x8a\xd8\xb3\xd8\xaa\xd8\xa7\xd9\x86\xd9\x8a</span>\xe2\x80\x8e\xe2\x80\x8e), born August 4, 1930, is an Iraqi <a href="/wiki/Usuli" title="Usuli">Usuli</a> <a href="/wiki/Marja%27" title="Marja\'">marja</a> in <a href="/wiki/Iraq" title="Iraq">Iraq</a> and the head of many of the <a href="/wiki/Hawza" title="Hawza">seminaries (Hawzahs)</a> in <a href="/wiki/Najaf" title="Najaf">Najaf</a>. Sistani was born in 1930 to a family of religious clerics, his father was Muhammad Baqir al-Sistani. Sistani himself claims to have been born in <a href="/wiki/Mashhad" title="Mashhad">Mashhad</a>, <a href="/wiki/Iran" title="Iran">Iran</a>, then moved to Mashhad as a child due to Iran not issuing birth certificates in its eastern provinces until decades later. After doing studies in Mashhad and <a href="/wiki/Qom" title="Qom">Qom</a>, In 1951, He traveled to <a href="/wiki/Iraq" title="Iraq">Iraq</a> to study in <a href="/wiki/Najaf" title="Najaf">Najaf</a> under Grand Ayatollah <a href="/wiki/Abu_al-Qasim_al-Khoei" title="Abu al-Qasim al-Khoei">Abu al-Qasim al-Khoei</a>. Sistani rose to the Usooli clerical rank of \'mujtahid\' in 1960. When Grand Ayatollah <a href="/wiki/Abu_al-Qasim_al-Khoei" title="Abu al-Qasim al-Khoei">Khoei</a> died in 1992, Sistani ascended to the rank of <a href="/wiki/Grand_Ayatollah" class="mw-redirect" title="Grand Ayatollah">Grand Ayatollah</a> through traditional peer recognition of his scholarship. His role as successor to Khoei was symbolically cemented when he led funeral prayers for Khoei; he also inherited Khoei\'s network and following.</p>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\n</div>\n<div style="clear: both; border: solid #2e8b57; border-width: 1px 1px 0; background: #31644d; color: #ffffff; padding: .1em;padding-top: .1em;padding-left: .1em;padding-right: .1em;padding-bottom: .1em;text-align: center;font-family: sans-serif;font-size:100%;margin-bottom: 0px;">\n<div class="plainlinks" style="float:right;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size:80%; color: #ffffff"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Quran/DYK/1&amp;action=edit"><span style="color: #ffffff">edit</span></a>&#160;&#160;</div>\n<h2 style="font-family:sans-serif; font-size:100%; font-weight:bold; border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em; color:#ffffff;"><span class="mw-headline" id="Did_you_know..."><i>Did you know...</i></span></h2>\n</div>\n<div style="border: 1px solid #2e8b57; border-top-width: 1px; vertical-align: top;background: #f8fffc;opacity: 1; color: #000000; text-align: left; margin: 0 0 10px; padding: 1em;padding-top: .3em;">\n<div style="float:right; margin-left:0.5em;" id="mp-dyk-img">\n<div class="thumbinner mp-thumb" style="background: transparent; border: none; padding: 0; max-width: 120px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Birmingham_Quran_manuscript_-_closeup.jpg" class="image" title="Close-up of the Birmingham Quran manuscript"><img alt="Close-up of the Birmingham Quran manuscript" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/57/Birmingham_Quran_manuscript_-_closeup.jpg/120px-Birmingham_Quran_manuscript_-_closeup.jpg" width="120" height="68" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/57/Birmingham_Quran_manuscript_-_closeup.jpg/180px-Birmingham_Quran_manuscript_-_closeup.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/57/Birmingham_Quran_manuscript_-_closeup.jpg/240px-Birmingham_Quran_manuscript_-_closeup.jpg 2x" data-file-width="624" data-file-height="351" /></a>\n<div class="thumbcaption" style="padding: 0.25em 0; word-wrap: break-word;">Close-up of the Birmingham Quran manuscript</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<ul>\n<li>... that the newly discovered <b><a href="/wiki/Birmingham_Quran_manuscript" title="Birmingham Quran manuscript">Birmingham Quran manuscript</a></b> <i>(pictured)</i> comprises fragments of an ancient <a href="/wiki/Quran" title="Quran">Quran</a> that may date to near Muhammad\'s lifetime?</li>\n<li>... that the story of the <b><a href="/wiki/People_of_the_Ditch" title="People of the Ditch">People of the Ditch</a></b>, mentioned in the <a href="/wiki/Quran" title="Quran">Quran</a>, occurred in 520 or 523 A.D in the time of <a href="/wiki/Dhu_Nuwas" title="Dhu Nuwas">Dhu Nuwas</a>, the last <a href="/wiki/Himyarite_Kingdom" title="Himyarite Kingdom">Himyarite</a> king?</li>\n</ul>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\n</div>\n<div style="clear: both; border: solid #2e8b57; border-width: 1px 1px 0; background: #31644d; color: #ffffff; padding: .1em;padding-top: .1em;padding-left: .1em;padding-right: .1em;padding-bottom: .1em;text-align: center;font-family: sans-serif;font-size:100%;margin-bottom: 0px;">\n<div class="plainlinks" style="float:right;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size:80%; color: #ffffff"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Qur%27an/Wikiprojects&amp;action=edit"><span style="color: #ffffff">edit</span></a>&#160;&#160;</div>\n<h2 style="font-family:sans-serif; font-size:100%; font-weight:bold; border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em; color:#ffffff;"><span class="mw-headline" id="WikiProjects"><i>WikiProjects</i></span></h2>\n</div>\n<div style="border: 1px solid #2e8b57; border-top-width: 1px; vertical-align: top;background: #f8fffc;opacity: 1; color: #000000; text-align: left; margin: 0 0 10px; padding: 1em;padding-top: .3em;">\n<dl>\n<dt>Parent project</dt>\n</dl>\n<p><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Islam" title="Wikipedia:WikiProject Islam">Islam</a></p>\n<div style="float:right;margin-left:0.9em"><a href="/wiki/File:Community.png" class="image" title="WikiProjects"><img alt="WikiProjects" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/c/ce/Community.png" width="50" height="33" data-file-width="48" data-file-height="32" /></a></div>\n<dl>\n<dt>Main project</dt>\n</dl>\n<p><b><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Qur%27an" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:WikiProject Qur\'an">Qur\'an</a></b></p>\n<div align="right">\n<p><b>What are <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:WikiProject" title="Wikipedia:WikiProject">WikiProjects</a>?</b></p>\n</div>\n<div style="margin:-.8em 0">\n<div class="noprint" style="margin:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; padding:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; text-align:right;"></div>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div style="float:right; width:100%">\n<div style="clear: both; border: solid #2e8b57; border-width: 1px 1px 0; background: #31644d; color: #ffffff; padding: .1em;padding-top: .1em;padding-left: .1em;padding-right: .1em;padding-bottom: .1em;text-align: center;font-family: sans-serif;font-size:100%;margin-bottom: 0px;">\n<div class="plainlinks" style="float:right;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size:80%; color: #ffffff"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Quran/Selected_quote/27&amp;action=edit"><span style="color: #ffffff">edit</span></a>&#160;&#160;</div>\n<h2 style="font-family:sans-serif; font-size:100%; font-weight:bold; border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em; color:#ffffff;"><span class="mw-headline" id="Selected_quote"><i>Selected quote</i></span></h2>\n</div>\n<div style="border: 1px solid #2e8b57; border-top-width: 1px; vertical-align: top;background: #f8fffc;opacity: 1; color: #000000; text-align: left; margin: 0 0 10px; padding: 1em;padding-top: .3em;">\n<p><strong class="error">The page "<a href="/w/index.php?title=Portal:Quran/Selected_quote/27&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Portal:Quran/Selected quote/27 (page does not exist)">Portal:Quran/Selected quote/27</a>" does not exist.</strong></p>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\n</div>\n<div style="clear: both; border: solid #2e8b57; border-width: 1px 1px 0; background: #31644d; color: #ffffff; padding: .1em;padding-top: .1em;padding-left: .1em;padding-right: .1em;padding-bottom: .1em;text-align: center;font-family: sans-serif;font-size:100%;margin-bottom: 0px;">\n<div class="plainlinks" style="float:right;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size:80%; color: #ffffff"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Qur%27an/Topics&amp;action=edit"><span style="color: #ffffff">edit</span></a>&#160;&#160;</div>\n<h2 style="font-family:sans-serif; font-size:100%; font-weight:bold; border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em; color:#ffffff;"><span class="mw-headline" id="Topics"><i>Topics</i></span></h2>\n</div>\n<div style="border: 1px solid #2e8b57; border-top-width: 1px; vertical-align: top;background: #f8fffc;opacity: 1; color: #000000; text-align: left; margin: 0 0 10px; padding: 1em;padding-top: .3em;">\n<center><i><b><a href="/wiki/Qur%27an" class="mw-redirect" title="Qur\'an">Qur\'an</a></b></i> <i>(<a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Books/Qur%27an" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:Books/Qur\'an">book</a>)</i></center>\n<p><b><a href="/wiki/Aqidah" title="Aqidah">Beliefs and practices</a>:</b> <a href="/wiki/Tawh%C4%ABd" class="mw-redirect" title="Tawh\xc4\xabd">Oneness</a> of <a href="/wiki/Islamic_concept_of_God" class="mw-redirect" title="Islamic concept of God">God</a> \xe2\x80\xa2 <a href="/wiki/Shahadah" class="mw-redirect" title="Shahadah">Profession of Faith</a> \xe2\x80\xa2 <a href="/wiki/Salat" class="mw-redirect" title="Salat">Prayer</a> \xe2\x80\xa2 <a href="/wiki/Sawm" class="mw-redirect" title="Sawm">Fasting</a> \xe2\x80\xa2 <a href="/wiki/Hajj" title="Hajj">Pilgrimage</a> \xe2\x80\xa2 <a href="/wiki/Zakat" title="Zakat">Charity</a></p>\n<div style="float:right;margin-left:1em"><a href="/wiki/File:Quran_cover.jpg" class="image" title="Islam topics"><img alt="Islam topics" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c3/Quran_cover.jpg/100px-Quran_cover.jpg" width="100" height="75" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c3/Quran_cover.jpg/150px-Quran_cover.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c3/Quran_cover.jpg/200px-Quran_cover.jpg 2x" data-file-width="2592" data-file-height="1944" /></a></div>\n<p><b><a href="/wiki/List_of_Muslims" class="mw-redirect" title="List of Muslims">Major figures</a>:</b> <a href="/wiki/Muhammad" title="Muhammad">Muhammad</a> \xe2\x80\xa2 <a href="/wiki/Abu_Bakr" title="Abu Bakr">Abu Bakr</a> \xe2\x80\xa2 <a href="/wiki/Umar" title="Umar">Umar</a> \xe2\x80\xa2 <a href="/wiki/Uthman" title="Uthman">Uthman</a> \xe2\x80\xa2 <a href="/wiki/Ali" title="Ali">Ali</a> \xe2\x80\xa2 <a href="/wiki/Sahaba" class="mw-redirect" title="Sahaba">Companions of Muhammad</a>\xe2\x80\xa2 <a href="/wiki/Ahl_al-Bayt" title="Ahl al-Bayt">Household of Muhammad</a> \xe2\x80\xa2 <a href="/wiki/Prophets_of_Islam" class="mw-redirect" title="Prophets of Islam">Prophets of Islam</a> \xe2\x80\xa2 <a href="/wiki/Shia_Imams" class="mw-redirect" title="Shia Imams">Shia Imams</a>\xe2\x80\xa2</p>\n<p><b><a href="/wiki/List_of_Islamic_texts" title="List of Islamic texts">Texts &amp; Laws</a>:</b> <a href="/wiki/Qur%27an" class="mw-redirect" title="Qur\'an">Qur\'an</a> \xe2\x80\xa2 <a href="/wiki/Hadith" title="Hadith">Hadith</a> \xe2\x80\xa2 <a href="/wiki/Sharia" title="Sharia">Sharia</a> \xe2\x80\xa2 <a href="/wiki/Fiqh" title="Fiqh">Jurisprudence</a> \xe2\x80\xa2 <a href="/wiki/Kalam" title="Kalam">Theology</a> \xe2\x80\xa2 <a href="/wiki/Sirat_Rasul_Allah" class="mw-redirect" title="Sirat Rasul Allah">Biographies of Muhammad</a></p>\n<p><b><a href="/wiki/Divisions_of_Islam" class="mw-redirect" title="Divisions of Islam">Branches of Islam</a>:</b> <a href="/wiki/Quranism" title="Quranism">Quranism</a> \xe2\x80\xa2 <a href="/wiki/Sunni_Islam" title="Sunni Islam">Sunni</a> \xe2\x80\xa2 <a href="/wiki/Shi%27a_Islam" class="mw-redirect" title="Shi\'a Islam">Shi\'a</a> \xe2\x80\xa2 <a href="/wiki/Sufism" title="Sufism">Sufi</a> \xe2\x80\xa2 <a href="/wiki/Ibadi" title="Ibadi">Ibadi</a> \xe2\x80\xa2 <a href="/wiki/Ahmadi" class="mw-redirect" title="Ahmadi">Ahmadi</a></p>\n<p><b><a href="/wiki/Muslim_culture" class="mw-redirect" title="Muslim culture">Sociopolitical aspects</a>:</b> <a href="/wiki/Islamic_studies" title="Islamic studies">Academics</a> \xe2\x80\xa2 <a href="/wiki/Islamic_philosophy" title="Islamic philosophy">Philosophy</a> \xe2\x80\xa2 <a href="/wiki/Islamic_art" title="Islamic art">Art</a> \xe2\x80\xa2 <a href="/wiki/Islamic_science" class="mw-redirect" title="Islamic science">Science</a> \xe2\x80\xa2 <a href="/wiki/Islamic_architecture" title="Islamic architecture">Architecture</a> \xe2\x80\xa2 <a href="/wiki/Islamic_calendar" title="Islamic calendar">Calendar</a>\xe2\x80\xa2 <a href="/wiki/Muslim_holidays" title="Muslim holidays">Holidays</a> \xe2\x80\xa2 <a href="/wiki/Women_in_Islam" title="Women in Islam">Women in Islam</a> \xe2\x80\xa2 <a href="/wiki/Islamic_religious_leaders" title="Islamic religious leaders">Leaders</a> \xe2\x80\xa2 <a href="/wiki/Political_aspects_of_Islam" title="Political aspects of Islam">Politics</a> \xe2\x80\xa2 <a href="/wiki/Islamic_Peace" class="mw-redirect" title="Islamic Peace">Islamic Peace</a>\xe2\x80\xa2 <a href="/wiki/Jihad" title="Jihad">Jihad</a> \xe2\x80\xa2 <a href="/wiki/Liberal_movements_within_Islam" class="mw-redirect" title="Liberal movements within Islam">Liberalism</a></p>\n<p><b>See also:</b> <a href="/wiki/List_of_Islamic_terms_in_Arabic" class="mw-redirect" title="List of Islamic terms in Arabic">Vocabulary of Islam</a>, <a href="/w/index.php?title=Category:Qur%27an&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Category:Qur\'an (page does not exist)">Index of articles on Qur\'an</a></p>\n<div style="margin:-.8em 0">\n<div class="noprint" style="margin:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; padding:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; text-align:right;"></div>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div style="clear: both; border: solid #2e8b57; border-width: 1px 1px 0; background: #31644d; color: #ffffff; padding: .1em;padding-top: .1em;padding-left: .1em;padding-right: .1em;padding-bottom: .1em;text-align: center;font-family: sans-serif;font-size:100%;margin-bottom: 0px;">\n<div class="plainlinks" style="float:right;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size:80%; color: #ffffff"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Quran/Featured_content&amp;action=edit"><span style="color: #ffffff">edit</span></a>&#160;&#160;</div>\n<h2 style="font-family:sans-serif; font-size:100%; font-weight:bold; border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em; color:#ffffff;"><span class="mw-headline" id="Featured_content"><i>Featured content</i></span></h2>\n</div>\n<div style="border: 1px solid #2e8b57; border-top-width: 1px; vertical-align: top;background: #f8fffc;opacity: 1; color: #000000; text-align: left; margin: 0 0 10px; padding: 1em;padding-top: .3em;">\n<p><a href="/w/index.php?title=Portal:Quran/Featured_content&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Portal:Quran/Featured content (page does not exist)">Portal:Quran/Featured content</a></p>\n<div style="margin:-.8em 0">\n<div class="noprint" style="margin:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; padding:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; text-align:right;"></div>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div style="clear: 